image.altText: A woman screams after scoring a goal.

items.synopsis: Scores are tied in Australia's crucial World Cup clash in Brisbane, after Nigeria answered a late Emily van Egmond goal in the first half. Follow the match live.

title.children: Nigeria levels things up just minutes after Matildas open the scoring

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Nigeria takes the lead. It came from a corner. The ball was headed around the area. Number 15 Rasheedat Ajibade heads towards keeper Mackenzie Arnold, who was unable to handle it cleanly. It hits her arm into the path of Osinachi Ohale who scores. Ohale has been injured in the goal since scoring.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 65': GOAL NIGERIA

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: The Matildas are on top but Nigeria are showing the same, stout defence they displayed against Canada. The final half-an-hour is going to be fun.
